<p>One of my favourite stories from the tour was about the statue up onÂ GellÃ©rt Hill. She was installed by the Soviets, but in the cleanup when the city decided to rid itself of all their statues, the people of Budapest apparently really liked the Liberation Monument and didnâ€™t want to get rid of her. The solution: Cover her up with a sheet for 3 days, thereafter unveiling her as if she were a new installation. Good on em, I say.</p>

<p style="text-align:center;">
  <a href="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/asiaeurope11/6621427571_310b9987a6_z.jpg"><img class="aligncenter" title="liberation monument" src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v236/mikezero/asiaeurope11/6621427571_310b9987a6_z.jpg" alt="" width="384" height="256" /></a>
